First, let's find the Cartesian product of A and B, denoted as A x B. This is the set of all ordered pairs (a, b) where a is an element of A and b is an element of B.

A x B = {(1, 2), (1, 4), (1, 6), (3, 2), (3, 4), (3, 6), (5, 2), (5, 4), (5, 6)}

Now let's find the symmetric difference of A and B, denoted as A⊕B. This is the set of elements that are in either A or B, but not in both.

A⊕B = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6}

Similarly, let's find the symmetric difference of B and A, denoted as B⊕A.

B⊕A = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6}

Now we need to find the symmetric difference of (A⊕B) and (B⊕A). Since A⊕B and B⊕A are the same sets, their symmetric difference will be the empty set, denoted as ∅.

(A⊕B)⊕(B⊕A) = ∅
